Principal Deputy National Security Advisor Jon Finer met with representatives of the three 2022 Nobel Peace Prize laureates at the White House. The laureates included Kanstantsin Staradubets for Belarusian political prisoner and activist Ales Bialiatski, Aleksandr Cherkasov for the Russian human rights organization Memorial Human Rights Center, and Oleksandra Matviichuk for the Ukrainian nonprofit the Center for Civil Liberties. The meeting focused on the importance of achieving a just and sustainable peace in Ukraine, along with democratic reforms and accountability for human rights violations. Mr. Finer praised the laureates for their contributions in their respective countries and emphasized the significance of defending human rights and freedoms globally. He also reiterated the U.S. Government's commitment to supporting Ukraine's defense of sovereignty and territorial integrity, as well as democracy and human rights worldwide, including support for civil society organizations.